      "role": "user",
      "content": "psychic armoring? i haven't heard that specific term before. it felt so much more physical than just \"intuition\" though. it was like a literal acoustic clash, like two notes that shouldn't be played together. do you think there's a way to actually measure or explain the physics of why a lie would cause that specific kind of frequency shift in someone's voice?",
